data.title: Count Vowels in a String
data.description: Write a function that takes a string as input and returns the number of vowels (a, e, i, o, u) in the string.

data.title: Calculate Power
data.description: Write a function that takes two integers, base and exponent, and calculates the value of base raised to the power of exponent.

data.title: Remove Duplicates from Array
data.description: Write a function that takes an array of integers as input and returns a new array without any duplicate elements.

data.title: Check Prime Number
data.description: Write a function that checks if a given number is a prime number. A prime number is a natural number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself.

data.title: Greatest Common Divisor
data.description: Write a function that takes two positive integers and returns their greatest common divisor (GCD).

data.title: Generate Fibonacci Series
data.description: Write a function that generates the Fibonacci series up to a specified number of terms. The Fibonacci series is a sequence of numbers in which each number is the sum of the two preceding ones, starting from 0 and 1.

data.title: Title Case a Sentence
data.description: Write a function that takes a sentence as input and returns the sentence with the first letter of each word capitalized.

data.title: Find Missing Number
data.description: Write a function that takes an array containing n distinct numbers taken from 0, 1, 2, ..., n, and finds the one that is missing from the array.

data.title: Calculate Factorial
data.description: Write a function that calculates the factorial of a non-negative integer using recursion. The factorial of a number is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to that number.

data.title: Rotate Array
data.description: Write a function that rotates an array to the right by a given number of steps. For example, if the array is [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] and the rotation steps is 2, the rotated array would be [4, 5, 1, 2, 3].

data.title: Check Anagrams
data.description: Write a function that checks if two given strings are anagrams of each other. Anagrams are words or phrases formed by rearranging the letters of a different word or phrase, typically using all the original letters exactly once.

data.title: Find Intersection of Two Arrays
data.description: Write a function that takes two arrays as input and returns an array containing their intersection. The intersection is the set of elements that are common to both arrays.

data.title: Count Words in a Sentence
data.description: Write a function that takes a sentence as input and returns the number of words in the sentence. Words are separated by spaces.

data.title: Calculate Square Root
data.description: Write a function that calculates the square root of a given non-negative integer. You may assume that the input is a perfect square.

data.title: Binary Search
data.description: Write a function that performs binary search on a sorted array of integers. The function should return the index of the target element if it exists in the array, or -1 otherwise.

data.title: Calculate Power of Two
data.description: Write a function that checks if a given number is a power of two. A number is a power of two if it is 2 raised to some integer power.

data.title: Check Balanced Parentheses
data.description: Write a function that checks if a given string of parentheses is balanced. Balanced parentheses mean that each opening parenthesis has a corresponding closing parenthesis and they occur in the correct order.
